}
{\plain\f4\fs21\i\cf2\ulc2
Appropriate expenditures.
}
{\plain\f4\fs21\cf2\ulc2
 The purpose of the funding described in Iowa Code section 257.45 is to provide for the needs of identified gifted and talented students beyond those needs that are provided by the regular school program. The funding shall be used only for expenditures directly related to providing the gifted and talented program described in the program plan. Appropriate expenditures are delineated in 281—Chapter 98.
}
